Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.60,0:33:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,identification of criminal suspects\Nwitnesses are wrong over 50% of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.44,0:33:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of the time\N55% of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.91,0:33:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of the time 50% of the time three\Npeople say I saw him do it now he's in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.79,0:33:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,prison and 50% of the time he's wrong.\NEven your own perception, you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.72,0:33:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,trust.\NEverybody's going to be a mess after
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.76,0:33:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,this lecture.\NCan't tell truth from spoof. You can't
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.24,0:34:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,believe your own lying eyes.\NCan't trust wrinkled old men. I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.67,0:34:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,know.\NAll right. How do we arrive at this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.52,0:34:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are several explanations.\NProbably the most the most uh profound
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.15,0:34:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of them and the one that I tend to agree\Nwith is uh the effect of karma. Yes. The
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.32,0:34:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,most profound effect of all is karma.\NMost profound effect of all is karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.80,0:34:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, "Well, Christianity uh doesn't\Nbelieve in karma. Western civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.48,0:34:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't believe in karma."\NChristianity does believe in karma. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.67,0:34:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the Garden of Eden. If it\Nwasn't for the garden, the fall of man
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.00,0:34:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Garden of Eden, you wouldn't need\Na savior. There wouldn't be any sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.96,0:35:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Though, what was the problem in the\NGarden of Eden? The problem is usually
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.56,0:35:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,presented as disobedience of God's edict\Nnot to eat of the tree of wisdom. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.76,0:35:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But the serpent came along and\Nsaid to the woman, "Eat. It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.35,0:35:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be fine."\NAnd she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.59,0:35:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the fall of man. And then they\Nnoticed they had no clothes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.80,0:35:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were naked and hid in shame.\NSo, how did that come about? What
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.24,0:35:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,explains the fall of man in that uh\Nhistoric tradition?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.80,0:35:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it evil? Was it disobedience? No. I\Nsee the innocence of Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.96,0:35:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What the serpent knew was the innocence,\Nthe inner innocence of the child. The
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.20,0:36:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,serpent said, "Oh, it'll be all right.\NTrust me, you this is a fine thing to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.28,0:36:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,do. And so the serpent wasn't saying\Ndefy God. The serpent was saying to the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.40,0:36:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,inner child and Eve, trust me,\Neverything will be fine. Yes. And that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.59,0:36:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was the beginning in the Christian\Ntradition then. So when they say
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.11,0:36:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity doesn't believe in karma,\Ndon't you believe them. If it wasn't for
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.72,0:36:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,original sin and the Garden of Eden,\Nthere wouldn't be any need for penance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.72,0:36:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't be any need for penance.\NThere'd be nothing to feel guilty about
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.59,0:36:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'd all be enlightened.\NWe'd all be enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.07,0:36:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So the serpent then was\Nthe source of falsehood. So falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.07,0:36:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,came in and spoofed Eve's innocence.\NAnd being herself an innocent woman, why
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.76,0:37:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,should she suspect that the serpent was\Nup to some nefarious intention?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.04,0:37:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why I teach about the serpent\Nto beware of the serpent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.80,0:37:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Beware of the serpent because that which\Nis cunning and sly and deceptive
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.40,0:37:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to be able to sense where you're\Nvulnerable. And that vulnerability
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.32,0:37:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,again is that intrinsically we all have\Nthe innocence of the child within us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.92,0:37:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The pure subjectivity of consciousness\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.32,0:37:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The structure of the mind is such that\Nit cannot tell one from another. The
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.04,0:37:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,computer, the mind's computer can become\Nprogrammed with falsehood as easily. So
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.48,0:37:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we all have intrinsically the innocence\Nof the computer. The computer doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.52,0:37:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Oh, I think I'll record this and\Nnot record this."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.20,0:38:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The computer of the human mind\Nautomatically
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.44,0:38:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,records all that it is presented with\Nwhether it's facious or true. It has no
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.68,0:38:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,means of discernment.\NSpiritual evolution then comes from
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.96,0:38:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,studying advanced spiritual teachings\Nand advancing by intention. So by one's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.56,0:38:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,intention one already is progressing\Nalready progressing by virtue of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.68,0:38:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,intention and then when one reaches a\Ncertain level of consciousness that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.20,0:38:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the that which is the sheep's\Nclothing and that which is innocence uh
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.80,0:38:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,become apparent. That's at level 600. At\Nlevel 600 the third eye of the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.28,0:38:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,body is what it's classically called.\NThat's when the atheric bodies of both
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.20,0:38:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the crown chakra\Nopens and now one instantly can
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.07,0:39:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize falsehood and deception. Yes.\NFrom that time on you're protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.32,0:39:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're protected by the presence of the\Ndivine spirit in the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.04,0:39:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern essence.\NSo that's the story of the garden of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.44,0:39:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Eden.\NBecause of the innocence. Because of the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.20,0:39:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,innocence. Then Christ taught that\Nsin is nothing but primarily ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.92,0:39:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sin is ignorance. Sin is error. So the\Noriginal meaning of the term sin is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.59,0:39:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,error. Error. To be an error.\NTo realize the innocence of the inner
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.16,0:39:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,child of everyone who exists.\NIt gives us a capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.32,0:39:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to be forgiving towards all people no\Nmatter what. So the person who thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.35,0:40:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that he's doing God a favor, worshiping\NGod by killing me
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.48,0:40:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'm a non-believer.\NI still recognize the, you know, the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.44,0:40:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,validity of his intention. If the way to\Nworship God is to kill all
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.48,0:40:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,non-believers,\Nthen I can see the innocence,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.76,0:40:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I differ with the correctness of it, but\NI can see the innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.80,0:40:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nif he kills you, you just say it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.83,0:40:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.\NThat's what we did. We did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.96,0:40:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you about a past life I remember\Nduring the Crusades. And this same
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.52,0:40:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,entity and I have had interactions over\Nmany lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.35,0:40:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I killed him for Jesus and he killed\Nme for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.24,0:40:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was during the Crusades through and\Nthrough and through and through and we
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.11,0:41:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,both fell over and our body went out of\Nthe physical body and we broke out
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.40,0:41:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,laughing at each other.\NHe said, "I did it for Allah." And I
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.56,0:41:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,said, "I did it for Jesus." And then we\Nlaughed and laughed and
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.28,0:41:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the naivity of the human mind as a out\Nof his devotion to God he killed me and
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.35,0:41:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I acknowledged that and therefore I've\Nhad great respect for that entity and uh
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.07,0:41:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we killed each other for God and for\Nso even those who blow us up even those
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.52,0:41:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who blow us up if they are doing it from\Nthat intention I can forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.00,0:41:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I'm not going to hang out with\Nthem
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.83,0:41:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,or invite them to lunch.\NWhat is it we're supposed to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.24,0:41:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,those people? There's some politically\Ncorrect thing. We're supposed to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.56,0:42:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,accommodate them. Yes. All right. All\Nright. Let other people accommodate
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.11,0:42:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,them. Frankly, I'm going to eat it in a\Ndifferent restaurant than where they
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.92,0:42:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,hang out.\NThis may be the day they're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.11,0:42:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,blow up the restaurant to get rid of all\Nthese.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.52,0:42:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth depends on con context.\NThe the overall intention then sets an
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.72,0:42:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,overall field. So the nonlinear sets the\Nfield whether a thing is good or evil
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.68,0:42:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be discerned by looking at the\Nthing itself but only in context. Only
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.59,0:42:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in context.\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.24,0:42:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah and we have in in today's society\Nof course the conspiracy theorists and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.76,0:42:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the logic proof delusional disorder. So\Nmany of society's problems you say they
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.96,0:42:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,closed the mental hospitals many years\Nago that was also cultural Marxism
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.20,0:42:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,come came through a guy named Thomas Zaz\Npopularized it to say that mental
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.16,0:43:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,illness was only a label\Nand therefore they closed all the mental
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.31,0:43:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,hospitals. So all the people who were\Ndangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.64,0:43:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,are now wandering the street and uh\Nkilling people right and left. So it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.56,0:43:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,used to be out of compassion that you\Nyou protected people from their own
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.56,0:43:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,limitation.\NI could tell them in if I let this guy
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.16,0:43:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,out, I know exactly what he's going to\Ndo. So it isn't just the safety of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.72,0:43:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,others. So the criteria was that this\Nperson is safe with his own self, the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.07,0:43:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity to survive and look after your\Nown basic needs. So some we kept in the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.83,0:43:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,hospital until they got well enough that\Nthey could survive on their own, that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.80,0:43:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,they had enough uh wits they could\Nsurvive on their own. So it wasn't just
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.83,0:43:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because of labeling, it was survival. So\Nnow they become drug addicted and and uh
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.76,0:44:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,hang out on the sidewalk and commit\Ncrimes and uh get murdered and murder
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.88,0:44:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,each other and they all end up in jail.\NSo we saw at the bottom of the list of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.11,0:44:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the levels of consciousness.\NThe average consciousness in prison is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.68,0:44:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,around 65. Yes. Is that right? The\Naverage consciousness in prison is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.56,0:44:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,around 65. Yeah, that's correct number.\NConsciousness level 65.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.35,0:44:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Can a person survive out there with a\Nconsciousness level of 65?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.28,0:44:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of humanitarian consideration, we'd\Nsay this person needs to be protected
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.07,0:44:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,until they're more capable of protecting\Nthemsel, remembering to take their
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.96,0:44:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,medication, remembering to see the\Ndoctor staying out of the way of crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.44,0:44:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. Yeah. So the intention then is the\Ngood and the welfare of all. The good
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.92,0:44:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the welfare all. So out of kindness.\NSo the one spiritual dictim that we stay
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.31,0:44:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,by is out of love and consideration and\Nreverence for all of life. And let that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.52,0:45:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,be the overall context of your own\Nvalition.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.31,0:45:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We the reason we do all that we do is\Nfor the for the good of all all. People
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.40,0:45:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "What can I do to, you know, help\Nhelp the world?" And um, well, you could
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.80,0:45:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,stay out of out of the way.\NGet off the highway. No,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.80,0:45:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the intention then the intention,\Nit's what you have become. So, we showed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.00,0:45:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,by the the chart we showed with the\Npyramid. It's what you have become that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.35,0:45:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,compensates for the negativity.\NSo, the negativity of the world would be
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.64,0:45:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so overwhelming. It would destroy\Nmankind except for people like
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.44,0:45:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,yourselves sitting here now. You realize\Nthat without you, millions would die.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.44,0:45:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions. Yes. Without this crowd here\Nassembled. This crowd here assembled. I
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.83,0:46:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have permission to ask this. Millions\Nwould die.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.00,0:46:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions would die were it not because\Nin the pyramid there's that small top.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.16,0:46:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's the balance, the little\Nbitty pyramid over here and the great
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.83,0:46:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,mass of mankind here to give greater\Nworth and value. That your spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.24,0:46:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,work, you know, is not just for your own\Nspiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.16,0:46:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,advancement.\NBut by seeking spiritual truth, you are
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.11,0:46:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,serving all of mankind\Nby your own search for enlightenment and
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.72,0:46:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for spiritual truth. You are serving all\Nof mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.07,0:46:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions would die were it not for you.\NBy your own search for enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.59,0:46:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you benefit all of mankind.\NYou benefit all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.64,0:46:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The depiction of a Buddhist type\Nmeditation is gazing at your own navl
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.83,0:47:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there for is incorrect.\NIt is for the good and the welfare of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.76,0:47:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,all mankind that we seek the highest\Ntruth and seek to become at one with
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.83,0:47:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that truth. We seek to become the\Nexpression of that truth. So as you pass
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.24,0:47:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,all be all beautiful things you\Nacknowledge their beauty and at a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.28,0:47:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,certain level of consciousness you have\Nto be care you have to actually avoid
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.88,0:47:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that because the beauty of things just\Nknocks you out. Just like a loving
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.68,0:47:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,glance between two people. It's just you\Ncannot handle it. It just makes you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.35,0:47:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,weep. And you you're careful not to look\Nat the flowers because they're stunning
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.16,0:47:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection.\NOh god. Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.72,0:47:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that was created by God.\NThat was created by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.52,0:48:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That flower\Nwas created by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.68,0:48:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So you sense the divinity\Nwithin all of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.31,0:48:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of reverence for divinity,\Nyou're then reverent towards all of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.80,0:48:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,creation,\Nall of a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.64,0:48:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,previous life. And you say to the\Nheadsman, don't feel about badly about
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.68,0:48:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're doing. It's your duty to the\Ncrown.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.83,0:48:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So you put your head on the block and as\Nthe headsman comes down, you bless them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.92,0:48:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing your duty. You recognize\Nit's his honor. It's his honor that he
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.80,0:48:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,serves the crown.\Nand people of that era. It was it was a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.48,0:48:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,mark of honor to serve the crown rather\Nthan your own personal self. So even the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.55,0:49:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,headspin as he comes over you can bless\Nhim
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.35,0:49:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you tell him don't feel badly about\Nwhat you're doing. You're a man of honor
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.00,0:49:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're serving the crown.\NHe goes home feeling happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.83,0:49:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Her\Nwife says, "Harold,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.52,0:49:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,how did it go today?"\NHe said,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.24,0:49:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,"That was her answer. How'd it go today,\NHarold?"
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.35,0:49:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Snap. Off it goes. You know, and we've\Ndemonstrated how if you live within the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.88,0:49:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,present instant, no such thing as a\Nproblem can arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.96,0:49:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Every instant is complete and total\Nwithin itself.
